      第 3 筆 ---------------------------------------------------------------------




系統識別號
U0026-0409201300481500


論文名稱(中文) 
      
歷史區域再生研究-臺南孔廟文化園區生活聚點建構與連結


論文名稱(英文) 
      
A Research on the Regeneration of Historical Area- Construction and Linkage of Living Space in Confucius Temple Cultural Zone in Tainan.


校院名稱
成功大學


系所名稱(中)
建築學系碩博士班


系所名稱(英)
Department of Architecture


學年度
101


學期
2


出版年
102


研究生(中文)
李昀蓁


學號
N76994075


學位類別
碩士


語文別
中文


口試日期
2013-06-13


論文頁數
150頁


口試委員
指導教授-陳世明
口試委員-陳正哲
口試委員-劉世南



關鍵字(中)
歷史區域再生生活文化歷史區域關係重構生活聚點在地與外來文化交流


關鍵字(英)
Regeneration of Historical AreaLiving CultureRelationship Reconstruction of Historical AreaLiving SpaceExchange between Local and Foreign Culture.


學科別分類



中文摘要
   臺南市歷史區域擁有特殊的地域性及地方感，居民長期在此生活衍生出別於其他城市的生活文化。過去歷史區域保存與再生的方式大多屬於單點保存及傳統博物館「凍結式」的保存，容易忽略在地生活者的日常生活與生活環境的關係。本研究以「生活環境博物館」之概念為背景，透過文獻整理與分析，提出對於歷史區域再生之新的方式與原則_生活聚點的建構與連結，以孔廟文化園區核心區域為對象，置入多個生活聚點並加以呈現。      歷史區域保存與再生中之原則，主要強調文化資產與居民之間的關係重構，以在地生活者角度出發，討論在地新文化的產生、在地居民與外來者之關係以及促成交流之可能性。依據上述原則加上區域特性提出新的空間可能性，空間未來機能以及經營管理機制，並且利用規劃設計手法呈現空間樣貌，提供軟體活動參考。     藉著臺南歷史區域中生活聚點的建構，歸納出以下三點，作為歷史區域再生發展的參考。 1. 　生活文化的呈現：透過生活聚點的建構，使得過去的生活文化及現在隱沒在社區中的在地生活文化得以在都市中較高層級據點呈現。 2.　新生活文化的形成：利用社區內部新的生活聚點支持或誘發其社區新文化的形成，讓在地文化得以持續性的發展。 3.　交流空間建構與經營：透過聚點的設置提供在地與外來文化交流之機會，瞭解歷史區域生活文化之內涵與價值。  【關鍵字】：歷史區域再生、生活文化、歷史區域關係重構、生活聚點、在地與外來文化交流。


英文摘要
	Tainan Historical area has special locality and sense of place. Combing with other cities, the residents who live here for a long time have developed different culture of life. In the past, the methodology of preservation and regeneration of historical area were mostly generated by focusing on individual site and traditional museum- freezing like preservation. As a result, the relationship between residential dairy life and environment has always been ignored. Through collating and analyzing document, this study uses Confucius Temple Cultural Zone as a target and bases on the concept of “ecomuseum” to propose a new way as well as principle of historical area regeneration: the construction and linkage of living space, and that is, to insert more than one living space as a methodology to generate this area. 	The principle of historical restoration and regeneration is mainly focusing on the reconstruction of relationship between cultural heritage and local inhabitants. It starts from local people’s position to discuss the birth of local culture; the relationship between local people and foreigners as well as the possibility of exchange appears. By combining the principle that mentioned above and adding the character of this area, this study proposes new possibilities of space, its future function and operation as well as management. What’s more, use planning design to visualize the space in order to provide references for making activities happened. 	Through the construction of living nodes in Tainan historical area, there are three points concluded and could be used as references for the development of historical area regeneration. They are as follow:  1.	The appearance of living culture    By constructing the living space, the local living culture, either vivid in the past or now hiding in the community, could be present in the higher urban hierarchy. 2. The formation of new local-living culture    Use new living nodes of community to support or to cause the formation of other new community culture in order to make local culture development sustainable.  3. The cultural exchange between local and foreign (external residents and tourists)    Through the exchange between “local– foreign” and “local- local”, we start to realize the value and spirit of living culture in historical area.


論文目次
