      第 16 筆 ---------------------------------------------------------------------




系統識別號
U0026-2208201220462900


論文名稱(中文) 
      
海軍空勤人員工作不安全感、組織承諾、離職傾向之關聯性研究－以個人與家庭特性為調節變項


論文名稱(英文) 
      
A Study of Relationship among Job Insecurity, Organizational Commitment and Turnover Intention for Navy Aircrew－Taking Individual and Family Characteristics as a Moderating Variable


校院名稱
成功大學


系所名稱(中)
企業管理學系專班


系所名稱(英)
Department of Business Administration (on the job class)


學年度
100


學期
2


出版年
101


研究生(中文)
朱樂恆


學號
r47991310


學位類別
碩士


語文別
中文


口試日期
2012-07-26


論文頁數
91頁


口試委員
指導教授-張淑昭
口試委員-陳淑惠
口試委員-王瑜琳



關鍵字(中)
工作不安全感組織承諾離職傾向空勤人員


關鍵字(英)
job insecurityorganizational commitmentturnover intentionaircrew


學科別分類



中文摘要
    在全球性的競爭化趨勢下，企業不斷地推動組織重組、併購、整合及精簡化等動作，國防部基於國防政策與國家財政運用考量，近年來陸續推動「精實案」、「精進案」，並規畫未來的「精粹案」。然而，其組織編制及工作內容的轉換並未隨著組織的精簡而遞減，據瞭解，由於軍士官的工作量負荷增加，造成軍士官離職意願增強，導致於核心業務無法銜接，相對的也造成單位士氣低落、人員的工作不安全感甚至離退等問題。本研究目的在探討工作不安全感對於組織承諾與離職傾向的影響程度及相互關聯性，以及工作不安全感藉由個人與家庭的特性調節對組織承諾的影響。    本研究以海軍空勤人員為研究對象，包含旋、定翼機飛行員、偵潛、機工、機務員等實際參與飛行任務者，問捲共發放300份，回收270份，無效問捲13份，有效問捲為257份，研究結果發現：（1）海軍空勤人員之工作不安全感知覺與組織承諾呈正向的顯著關係。（2）海軍空勤人員之組織承諾與離職傾向呈負向顯著關係。（3）海軍空勤人員之工作不安全感與離職傾向呈負向顯著關係。（4）空勤人員組織承諾在工作不安全感對離職傾向具有部分中介效果。（5）空勤人員個人與家庭特性對工作不安全感與離職傾向間沒有調節效果。最後，本研究依研究結果加以探討說明並對學術及實務上的管理意涵提供建議。


英文摘要
In the trend of global competition, corporations continue to promote reorganization, merger, integration, and streamlining actions. Based on the national defense policy and the consideration of the national financial employment, in recent years, the Department of Defense has constantly set into actions of “Jingshih Program (The ROC Armed Forces Strengthening Program)”, “Jingjin Program (The ROC Armed Forces Refining Program)”, and “Jingtsui program” which is for the planning of the future. However, the conversion of the organization and the job contents did not decrease along with the streamlining of the organization. We understand that due to the increase of officer’s workload resulting in officer’s resignation intention gets stronger; which led to the core operations can not be engaged with and relatively caused other issues of low morality, job insecurity, and even resignation and retirement. This study aims to explore the impact and interrelation of job insecurity on the organizational commitment and turnover intention, as well as the impact of job insecurity on organizational commitment through the characteristic adjustment of individuals and families.The research object is the Navy aircrew including those actually participating in missions of spin and fixed-wing pilots, scouts, and mechanics. A total of 300 questionnaires were distributed, 270 recovered, 13 invalid and the total valid questionnaires are 257. The research results showed that: (1) there is a positive significant relationship between the sense of Navy aircrew’s job insecurity and the organizational commitment. (2) There is a negative significant relationship between Navy aircrew’s organizational commitment and turnover intention. (3) There is a negative relationship between Navy aircrew’s job insecurity and turnover intention. (4) There is partial mediation of aircrew’s organizational commitment on job insecurity versus turnover intention. (5) There is no moderating effect of aircrew’s individual and family characteristics on job insecurity and turnover intention. Finally, this study provides relevant recommendations in accordance with the findings, and discusses academic and practical management implications.


